Ask HN: Why Is Instagram Killing Itself?
text:
Over the past few weeks there have been a number of inexplicable 'bugs' with Instagram. An example I'll use is browsing by hashtag is no longer possible unless you are using the app (previously, it was possible to browse via browser).

My question for HN, and more specifically for IG developers on HN, is why are you disabling features?

It would be understandable if the rationale was to drive traffic to the app, but no error saying 'you must use the app to browse by hashtag' is displayed when you try browsing on a browser, you just get a page showing the top posts, with no explanation why other posts are there. So that reason doesn't cut it.
